cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.CL, cs.NE 

The paper deals with deep generative models and their application to semi-supervised classification. This falls under the broad category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The experiments involve image datasets, which suggests computer vision (cs.CV) as a likely sub-category. The classification task also involves natural language processing, which could lead to the inclusion of computational linguistics (cs.CL) as a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper proposes a novel algorithm for inference, which could be relevant to the sub-category of neural networks (cs.NE).
